QLAC — a low-latency lossless audio codec
Copyright (C) 2025  Leonardo Severi

========================================================================
Overview
========================================================================

QLAC is a fork of libFLAC 1.5.0, the reference FLAC codec library, which
is distributed under the Xiph.Org BSD-like license (a BSD-3-Clause-family
license). QLAC is distributed under the same BSD-3-Clause / Xiph-style
terms.

The QLAC source tree combines two bodies of code:

  1. files derived from libFLAC 1.5.0, and
  2. original QLAC files written for this project.

Every source file states in its header which of the two applies to it.
The per-file provenance table in FORK_NOTES.md records, for each file,
whether it is FLAC-derived or QLAC-original and what was changed.

========================================================================
1. FLAC-derived files
========================================================================

Files derived from libFLAC 1.5.0 retain the copyright of their original
authors:

    Copyright (C) 2000-2009  Josh Coalson
    Copyright (C) 2011-2025  the Xiph.Org Foundation

These files remain licensed under the Xiph.Org BSD-like license, the full
text of which is reproduced in the file COPYING.Xiph in this
distribution.

Two kinds of change were made to these files for QLAC:

  - Mechanical renames, principally the renaming of the FLAC__* symbol
    namespace to QLAC__*.

  - In some files, substantial modifications beyond mechanical renaming.

All such modifications are:

    Copyright (C) 2025  Leonardo Severi

and are contributed under the same Xiph.Org BSD-like terms that already
govern the file (COPYING.Xiph). The original copyright and license
notices in these files are retained.

========================================================================
2. Original QLAC files
========================================================================

Files written originally for QLAC (for example, the added block-codec
code) are:

    Copyright (C) 2025  Leonardo Severi

and are licensed under the 3-clause BSD license, the full text of which
is reproduced in the file COPYING.QLAC in this distribution.

========================================================================
Relationship between the two licenses
========================================================================

Both COPYING.Xiph and COPYING.QLAC are members of the BSD-3-Clause
license family and impose the same substantive conditions:

  - redistributions must retain the copyright notice, this list of
    conditions, and the warranty disclaimer;
  - the names of the copyright holders and contributors may not be used
    to endorse or promote derived products without prior written
    permission;
  - the software is provided "as is", without warranty, and the
    copyright holders and contributors are not liable for damages.

They differ only in the named copyright holder. The combined work may be
redistributed under these terms.

========================================================================
Where to look
========================================================================

  FORK_NOTES.md   Per-file provenance table (FLAC-derived vs.
                  QLAC-original, and what changed in each file).
  COPYING.Xiph    Full text of the Xiph.Org BSD-like license
                  (FLAC-derived files).
  COPYING.QLAC    Full text of the QLAC 3-clause BSD license
                  (QLAC-original files and QLAC modifications).
  NOTICE          Concise attribution and funding acknowledgment.
  AUTHORS         Authorship and contributor credits.
